Steps to Start Mongo Server:

After installing MongoDB and Mongo-java-driver-3.8.0.jar, create database and log directories.
Command- md "\data\db" "\data\log"

Start MongoDB database
"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.0\bin\mongod.exe" --dbpath="c:\data\db"

In another command prompt, connect to MongoDB
"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\4.0\bin\mongo.exe"

Steps to run the Applications
To run this weather application, we need the following jar files:
json-simple-1.1.jar
jcommon-1.0.23.jar
jfreechart-1.0.19.jar
mongo-java-driver-3.8.0.jar

To add all these jars to your project's class path, right click on the project, go to properties -> libraries. Click on "Add JAR/Folder" and select the required jar files.

Run WeatherInfo.java file to run the application.


